Incident Response > [T3]: Lab - Suricata: Detect malicious traffic

Detect malicious traffic using Suricata as an IDS

Suricata's primary purpose is to detect and prevent network-level attacks based on pre-defined signatures. In this module, we will perform a Nmap scan using the http-enum script and show how Suricata will alert on that traffic.

First, let us tail Suricata's fast.log file, which will contain our log to the suspicious traffic:

sudo tail -n0 -f /var/log/suricata/fast.log

Then we will fire the Nmap scan against the cyberdefenders.org domain:

nmap --script http-enum cyberdefenders.org  -p80

As you can see in the below screenshot, Suricata successfully detected a web application attack based on a signature that matched against Nmap User-Agent.
